definitions.definition: Any of the diverse group of eukaryotes , of the phylum Protozoa , that are primarily unicellular , existing singly or aggregating into colonies, are usually nonphotosynthetic , and are often classified further into phyla according to their capacity for and means of motility , as by pseudopods , flagella , or cilia .

main_definition: ( cytology ) Any of the diverse group of eukaryotes , of the phylum Protozoa , that are primarily unicellular , existing singly or aggregating into colonies, are usually nonphotosynthetic , and are often classified further into phyla according to their capacity for and means of motility , as by pseudopods , flagella , or cilia .
